"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773088","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-26","<p>The Government published its assessment of the impacts of the alcohol duty changes in the Tax Information and Impact Note, which can be found online at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/alcohol-duty-rate-changes/alcohol-duty-rate-changes" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/alcohol-duty-rate-changes/alcohol-duty-rate-changes</a></p><p> </p><p>The Treasury keeps all taxes under review and engages with a wide variety of organisations to understand industry developments, including the beer and pub industry and public health groups.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","108562","2017-10-26T14:30:31.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773088/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773088/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773088/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-18","Beer: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of the beer duty increases announced in the March 2017 Budget on beer consumption in the (a) on-trade and (b) off-trade.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","108561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773089","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-26","<p>The Government published its assessment of the impacts of the alcohol duty changes in the Tax Information and Impact Note, which can be found online at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/alcohol-duty-rate-changes/alcohol-duty-rate-changes" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/alcohol-duty-rate-changes/alcohol-duty-rate-changes</a></p><p> </p><p>The Treasury keeps all taxes under review and engages with a wide variety of organisations to understand industry developments, including the beer and pub industry and public health groups.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","108561","2017-10-26T14:30:31.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773089/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773089/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773089/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-18","Beer: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of changes in beer duty on the cost of beer production.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","108562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773090","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>Up to £1.5bn has already been allocated to the Equitable Life Payment Scheme to pay to policyholders. There are no plans to reopen the Payment Scheme or to allocate further funds to it.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-10-24T14:13:08.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773090/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773090/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773090/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-18","Equitable Life Assurance Society: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he or a Minister of his Department will meet with the Equitable Members Action Group to discuss the level of payments made available to policyholders in relation to the relative losses suffered as a result of past government and regulatory maladministration.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","108608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773091","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-26","<p>The employment rate in the North East is near its record high at 72.2%; the unemployment rate is 5.8%; weekly earnings for an average full-time employee are £504; and nominal Gross Value Added (GVA) per head has grown 13.7% since 2010. The gap between the North East and the UK employment rate has narrowed over the past two years.</p><p> </p><p>The government is addressing the barriers to economic growth in the North East and the rest of the Northern Powerhouse by investing in skills and infrastructure, developing our Industrial Strategy, and devolving more powers to local areas including the Tees Valley Combined Authority. This builds on the £379.6 million Local Growth Fund awarded to the North East since 2014.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-10-26T16:53:06.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773091/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773091/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773091/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-18","Economic Situation and Employment: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the reasons for disparities in (a) employment, (b) unemployment, (c) average earnings and (d) economic growth in North East England.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen Hepburn","Jarrow","Mr Stephen Hepburn","108532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773092","Department for Education","false","2017-10-26","<p>Kinship carers’ access to financial support depends on the individual circumstances of the carer and the child. This includes whether the arrangement in place is formal or informal and whether a child in an informal arrangement is recognised as being ‘in need’ under s17 of the Children Act 1989.</p><p>The Children Act 1989 sets out the duties and responsibilities of local authorities to support the needs of all children living with family and friends carers. Statutory guidance “Children Act 1989: family and friends care”, published during the last Parliament, strengthened the requirements on local authorities to support families and friends caring arrangements, including on financial support.</p><p>The guidance is available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/children-act-1989-family-and-friends-care" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/children-act-1989-family-and-friends-care</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-26T16:38:42.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773092/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773092/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773092/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-18","Carers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that kinship carers have sufficient financial support.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","108447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773093","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-26","<p>The government is committed to making the welfare system fair for those who pay for it as well as those who benefit from it. Families in receipt of welfare payments should face the same financial decisions as families supporting themselves solely through work. However, in recognition that some claimants are not able to make choices about the number of children in their family, the government has provided exceptions for certain groups, including in cases of kinship care.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the exceptions will be published at a future date following quality assurance.</p><p> </p><p>As with all our policies, the government will continue to keep this policy under review.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","108635","2017-10-26T10:48:33.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773093/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773093/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773093/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-18","Carers: Child Tax Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will bring forward proposals to remove the two child tax credit limit for kinship carers who are unable to claim child tax credit for any child to whom they give birth.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","108448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773094","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-23","<p>The amount of funding which will be made available in the upcoming round of LIBOR grants, ‘LIBOR 2017’, has yet to be confirmed.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-10-23T09:59:13.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773094/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773094/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773094/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-18","Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much funding will be made available for charities in the upcoming round of Libor funding.","false","Biography information for Johnny Mercer","Plymouth, Moor View","Johnny Mercer","108462"
