"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773097","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-23","<p>The government keeps all taxes under review at fiscal events, and we will consider this issue carefully as part of the Autumn Budget process.</p><p> </p><p>This government is aware of concerns about Small Brewers Relief, it has invited views on how it can be reformed in a way that the whole sector could support.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-10-23T14:39:56.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773097/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773097/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773097/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-18","Beer: Small Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will review the operation of the small brewer relief scheme to ensure there are no barriers to growth for small and medium-sized brewers.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","108362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773098","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-23","<p>The Government published its assessment of the impacts of the alcohol duty changes in the Tax Information and Impact Note, which can be found online at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/alcohol-duty-rate-changes/alcohol-duty-rate-changes" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/alcohol-duty-rate-changes/alcohol-duty-rate-changes</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Treasury keeps all taxes under review and engages with a wide variety of organisations to understand industry developments, including the beer and pub industry and public health groups.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","108377","2017-10-23T14:36:05.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773098/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773098/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773098/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-18","Beer and Public Houses: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect on (a) jobs and (b) investment in the Scottish brewing and pubs sector as a result of the 3.9 per cent increase in beer duty announced in the Budget 2017.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","108378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773099","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-23","<p>The Government published its assessment of the impacts of the alcohol duty changes in the Tax Information and Impact Note, which can be found online at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/alcohol-duty-rate-changes/alcohol-duty-rate-changes" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/alcohol-duty-rate-changes/alcohol-duty-rate-changes</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Treasury keeps all taxes under review and engages with a wide variety of organisations to understand industry developments, including the beer and pub industry and public health groups.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","108378","2017-10-23T14:36:05.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773099/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773099/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773099/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-18","Beer: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect on beer prices of the 3.9 per cent increase in beer duty announced in the Budget 2017.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","108377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773100","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-26","<p>We are currently undertaking a Fair Funding Review to address concerns about the fairness of current funding distributions to local authorities. There have been widespread calls for a thorough, evidence-based Review, and this we plan to deliver.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-10-26T13:24:49.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773100/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773100/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773100/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Local Government Finance: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to review the local government funding settlement in order to ensure parity of funding per head of population between London boroughs.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","108395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773101","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-26","<p>Through the Fair Funding Review we are working closely with the Local Government Association and representatives from across local government to ensure that we consider all the issues that impact on authorities’ relative need to spend on services and their capacity to fund these from local resources.</p><p>Amongst the issues we will consider are the impact of population growth, deprivation, and specific geographical factors such as rurality and area-related costs.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-10-26T13:24:26.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773101/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773101/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773101/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to review the criteria for the local government funding settlement to ensure that it includes (a) up to date information on population growth and (b) levels of deprivation in each local authority area.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","108396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773102","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-24","<p>The National Planning Policy Framework recognises the significant contribution that aviation makes to economic growth. It requires local authorities, when preparing their Local Plans, to take account of the role of airfields in meeting business, leisure, training and emergency service needs. Planning guidance supporting the Framework makes clear local authorities should consider the interconnectivity between airfields of different sizes and that they should have regard to the Aviation Policy Framework.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-24T10:07:33.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773102/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773102/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773102/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Airports: Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to include protection for airfields in the National Planning Policy Framework.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","108384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773103","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-10-25","<p>The Government is committed to tackling fly-tipping on a number of fronts. In 2015 we gave local authorities stronger powers to stop, seize and destroy vehicles of those suspected of fly-tipping. It is the responsibility of local authorities to use the powers available to them. The National Fly-tipping Prevention Group has published guidance for local authorities which sets out clearly the powers available to local authorities and other partners when tackling fly-tipping.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-10-25T09:21:37.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773103/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773103/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773103/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-18","Fly Tipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps he is taking to ensure that local authorities use their powers to seize motor vehicles involved in fly-tipping.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","108441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773104","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-23","<p>There are many factors that contribute to a claimant falling into arrears or becoming homeless. DWP has no plans to carry out such an assessment.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-23T10:52:51.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773104/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773104/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773104/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-18","Local Housing Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 16 October 2017 to Question 106777, if he will carry out an assessment of the effect of the freezing of the rate of local housing allowance on the rate at which housing benefit recipients (a) fall into rent arrears and (b) become homeless.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","108437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773105","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-01","<p>We do not have exact figures on this but I am aware that a small number of local authorities continue to issue their newsletters more frequently than the Publicity Code says they should.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-11-01T14:12:11.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773105/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773105/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773105/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Local Government: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what information his Department holds on which local authorities publish magazines or newsletters for the public more than four times a year.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","108481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773106","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-01","<p>To provide all the correspondence between my Department and the Local Government Association, on fire safety in the last 3 months, would place a disproportionate cost on the Department.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-01T16:22:54.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773106/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773106/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773106/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will place in the Library copies of all correspondence between his Department and the Local Government Association on fire safety in the last 3 months.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","108490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773107","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-31","<p>My officials and I meet regularly with letting and managing agents and their representatives, including the Residential Landlords Association (RLA), the National Approved Letting Scheme (NALS) and the Association of Residential Managing Agents (ARMA). A full list of all ministerial meetings with external bodies on departmental business is publicly available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dclg-ministerial-data/" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dclg-ministerial-data/</a>.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-31T15:29:16.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773107/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773107/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773107/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Letting Agents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to his Department's call for evidence of 18 October 2017, on protecting consumers in the letting and managing agent market, what meetings he and Ministers in his Department have had with industry bodies on the letting and management industry since 1 January 2017.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","108568"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773108","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-31","<p>We will be publishing our response to the consultation and the Tenant Fees Bill shortly. We will provide more information on the implementation timetable following scrutiny of the draft Bill.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-31T15:31:12.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773108/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773108/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773108/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Letting Agents: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to his Department's call for evidence of 18 October 2017, on protecting consumers in the letting and managing agent market, when he plans for legislative proposals to be (a) introduced and (b) come into force to ban letting agent fees.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","108567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773109","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-31","<p>The call for evidence closes on 29 November 2017. We will use the evidence received through this exercise to help shape proposals, including legislative proposals where necessary and will provide further details in due course.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","108566","2017-10-31T15:30:16.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773109/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773109/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773109/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Private Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to his Department's call for evidence of 18 October 2017 on protecting consumers in the letting and managing agent market, when he plans for legislative proposals on such protection to (a) be introduced and (b) take effect.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","108565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773110","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-27","<p>The Government is committed to the principles of the Accelerated Construction programme. These principles include using Modern Methods of Construction, partnering with small and medium-sized builders, contractors and others, to increase the pace of construction on surplus public sector land.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-27T14:36:43.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773110/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773110/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773110/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what his policy is on the previous government's Accelerated Construction programme.","false","Biography information for Darren Jones","Bristol North West","Darren Jones","108557"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773111","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-27","<p>An impact assessment will be provided in due course and a copy will be placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-27T11:25:14.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773111/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773111/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773111/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Letting Agents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to his Department's report, Protecting consumers in the letting and managing agent market: call for evidence, published in October 2017, if he will place a copy of any impact assessment conducted on the proposals in the call for evidence in the Library.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","108616"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773112","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-31","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p><p>As we made clear in the publication referred to by the Rt Hon Member for Wentworth and Dearne, lettings and management agents do not have to be registered. There is therefore no official Government figure of the number of these agents that exist.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-31T15:29:42.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773112/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773112/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773112/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Letting Agents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the publication Protecting consumers in the letting and managing agent market: call for evidence, how many letting and management agents operate in England.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","108571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773113","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-31","<p>The call for evidence closes on 29 November 2017. We will use the evidence received through this exercise to help shape proposals, including legislative proposals where necessary and will provide further details in due course.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","108565","2017-10-31T15:30:17.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773113/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773113/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773113/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-18","Letting Agents: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to his Department's call for evidence of 18 October 2017 on protecting consumers in the letting and managing agent market, what the average reduction in service charges will be for leaseholders in the event that the proposals in that call for evidence are brought into force.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","108566"
